14 Should apes be saved from Ebola?
http://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2015/09/chimpanzees-gorillas-ebola-vaccine/405043/
[Scientists and conservationists can't agree on which is a larger threat to chimpanzees: the disease, or the medical research that might lead to an animal vaccine for it...
...Hard numbers are hard to come by, but some conservationists estimate Ebola has wiped out around 1/3rd of the world's wild chimpanzees and gorillas over the past few decades. ...more]

